      "writtenOn": "2020-01-22T19:41:52Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "To expand on my earlier feedback with some concrete examples, this is how I would name the various test cases for NewHandlers:\n\n  TestNewHandlers_BaselineSubset_emptyHandlersConfig_returnsError\n  TestNewHandlers_BaselineSubset_handlersConfigWithBaselineSubsetFieldsSet_success\n  TestNewHandlers_BaselineSubset_handlersConfigWithAllFieldsSet_success\n  TestNewHandlers_FullFrontend_emptyHandlersConfig_returnsError\n  TestNewHandlers_FullFrontend_handlersConfigWithBaselineSubsetFieldsSet_returnsError\n  TestNewHandlers_FullFrontend_handlersConfigWithAllFieldsSet_success\n\nHopefully the motivation behind the testName_input_expectedOutput naming convention as in http://go/unit-test-practices#naming makes more sense now.\n\nThe same idea would apply for table-driven tests.\n\nTo be clear, I\u0027m also implying that I\u0027d prefer this test to be broken into multiple smaller tests. But that\u0027s probably out of scope.\n\nWhat do you think?",
